>> title: Spiced Roasted Chickpeas
>> cuisine: Mediterranean
>> tags: snack, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 4
>> yield: 2 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: room-temp
>> reheat: Serve at room temperature.

-- Key to crispiness: dry the chickpeas VERY well

Preheat #oven{} to 400°F (200°C).

Pat @chickpeas{1%can}(15 oz, drained and rinsed) VERY dry with #paper towels{}.

Toss with @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Spread on #sheet pan{} in single layer.

Roast ~{35-40%minutes}, shaking pan every 10 minutes, until golden and crispy.

Immediately toss with @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @cayenne{1/4%tsp}, and @kosher salt{1/2%tsp} while hot.

Let cool completely before storing. They'll crisp up more as they cool.

-- Store in airtight container at room temperature
